.SH "NAME"
ir\-X \- reads the file created by showtherm and draws a picture on the screen, in an X\-windows environment, giving an appropriate color to each pixel based on the temperature
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBir\-X\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTIONS"
.sp
\fBir\-X\fP is an interactive program that reads the information in
the file created by \fBshowtherm\fP and then draws an image on the
screen.  The color of each pixel is based on the temperature of the
region that pixel belongs to.
.sp
\fBir\-X\fP is designed to be run in an X\-windows environment.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.sp
The following is an example from an interactive session.
.sp
